{"componentChunkName":"component---src-pages-index-jsx","path":"/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Artem Demo, indie developer","description":"Blog about web development, indie GameDev"}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"totalCount":39,"edges":[{"node":{"excerpt":"One of the challenging issues with in-game explosions - is to decide how you’ll deal damage to the player.\nFirst, it should be an area damage and regardless of the player’s position he should receive damage (if he stays close enough).","fields":{"slug":"/20210201-2d-platformer-explosion-wave-in-unity/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"04 February, 2021","title":"2D explosion wave in unity","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/3e4a6418d6cdcb9794b6afea3565cebd/d966b/explosion-wave-thumbnail.png","srcSet":"/static/3e4a6418d6cdcb9794b6afea3565cebd/46a2d/explosion-wave-thumbnail.png 30w,\n/static/3e4a6418d6cdcb9794b6afea3565cebd/156de/explosion-wave-thumbnail.png 60w,\n/static/3e4a6418d6cdcb9794b6afea3565cebd/d966b/explosion-wave-thumbnail.png 120w","sizes":"(max-width: 120px) 100vw, 120px"}}}}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Lately I finished the “Designing Games”, by Tynan Sylvester, lead developer of Rimworld.\nHighly recommend to everyone who is interested in game design.\nThis book is not about the code, but about experience that your game will create.","fields":{"slug":"/20210130-designing-games-book/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"30 January, 2021","title":"Designing Games, book by Tynan Sylvester","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/1904225e7f0a469042f4fdb39a6e237f/6e81a/designing-games-thumbnail.jpg","srcSet":"/static/1904225e7f0a469042f4fdb39a6e237f/b2a33/designing-games-thumbnail.jpg 30w,\n/static/1904225e7f0a469042f4fdb39a6e237f/0b3e1/designing-games-thumbnail.jpg 60w,\n/static/1904225e7f0a469042f4fdb39a6e237f/6e81a/designing-games-thumbnail.jpg 120w","sizes":"(max-width: 120px) 100vw, 120px"}}}}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"If you used tiles in your game, you know what I’m talking about. Usually its white lines, but they can be of any color, and it can drive you crazy.\nIt looks like that the problem is related to how unity allocates tiles from your sprites.\nWhile the camera moves in a scene the game engine rerender the scene and from time to time it doesn’t draw exactly the tile at exactly the place.  IMO it’s the result of optimizations on the unity side, but nevertheless we need a way to solve it.\nI found two…","fields":{"slug":"/20210128-vertical-lines-between-tiles/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"28 January, 2021","title":"Vertical lines between tiles in tile map in unity","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/0f0f9509ff3f97b779c2399c479b1b92/d966b/vertical-line-between-tiles-thumbnail.png","srcSet":"/static/0f0f9509ff3f97b779c2399c479b1b92/46a2d/vertical-line-between-tiles-thumbnail.png 30w,\n/static/0f0f9509ff3f97b779c2399c479b1b92/156de/vertical-line-between-tiles-thumbnail.png 60w,\n/static/0f0f9509ff3f97b779c2399c479b1b92/d966b/vertical-line-between-tiles-thumbnail.png 120w","sizes":"(max-width: 120px) 100vw, 120px"}}}}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"TL;DR Do not relay on colliders for fast moving objects.\nYou need to use “Physics.Raycast” to determine when a collision took place.","fields":{"slug":"/20210118-unity-object-moves-too-fast-for-the-collider-to-catch/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"18 January, 2021","title":"Object moves too fast for the collider to catch (solution for unity)","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/651fb9e954d306fd7859e4264c715edc/d966b/oldman-attack-illustration-thumbnail.png","srcSet":"/static/651fb9e954d306fd7859e4264c715edc/46a2d/oldman-attack-illustration-thumbnail.png 30w,\n/static/651fb9e954d306fd7859e4264c715edc/156de/oldman-attack-illustration-thumbnail.png 60w,\n/static/651fb9e954d306fd7859e4264c715edc/d966b/oldman-attack-illustration-thumbnail.png 120w","sizes":"(max-width: 120px) 100vw, 120px"}}}}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"I started experimenting with game development. For now, it’s a hobby, we’ll see how it will go :)","fields":{"slug":"/20210103-game-experiment/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"09 January, 2021","title":"I started new game experiment","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/e44d0d952b434de8556b694bd2a1f852/d966b/first-screenshot-thumbnail.png","srcSet":"/static/e44d0d952b434de8556b694bd2a1f852/46a2d/first-screenshot-thumbnail.png 30w,\n/static/e44d0d952b434de8556b694bd2a1f852/156de/first-screenshot-thumbnail.png 60w,\n/static/e44d0d952b434de8556b694bd2a1f852/d966b/first-screenshot-thumbnail.png 120w","sizes":"(max-width: 120px) 100vw, 120px"}}}}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"I decided to add diversity in everyday developers’ life and last month I started to learn a new thing - pixel art.\nIt was long waiting goal, but finally I found time to invest in it (thanks you to all lockdowns, I guess).","fields":{"slug":"/20210101-learning-pixel-art/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"01 January, 2021","title":"I started to learn pixel art","featuredImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/a224bb8a8dc7853ae014f569f8cf3790/d966b/pixel-art-thumbnail.png","srcSet":"/static/a224bb8a8dc7853ae014f569f8cf3790/46a2d/pixel-art-thumbnail.png 30w,\n/static/a224bb8a8dc7853ae014f569f8cf3790/156de/pixel-art-thumbnail.png 60w,\n/static/a224bb8a8dc7853ae014f569f8cf3790/d966b/pixel-art-thumbnail.png 120w","sizes":"(max-width: 120px) 100vw, 120px"}}}}}},{"node":{"excerpt":"Today is an important milestone - I create favicon for my website (the one you’re viewing right now) 🎉","fields":{"slug":"/20201029-adding-favicon-to-gatsby-site/"},"frontmatter":{"date":"29 October, 2020","title":"Adding favicon to gatsby website","featuredImage":{